passages.text: F1Q26 First ImpressionsBFb just reported F1Q26 EPS of \(0.36\), which landed between our \(0.35\) and Consensus \(0.37\). An estimated \(\sim 3c\) below- the- line drag vs. our model (namely an early retirement benefit expense) was equally offset by higher other income reported above the line.

Our ThoughtsStrong shipments ahead of the JD Blackberry innovation launch planned for late summer proved to be a tailwind during the quarter. After adjusting for the 4- point benefit to topline from the net change in distributor inventories, BFB's OSG appears more in line with our approx. \(- 3\%\) forecast, with some puts and takes across the footprint as emerging outperformed and developed international lagged vs. our expectations. US organic sales came in softer than our forecast ex. the 6- point tailwind from distributor inventory changes that stemmed from the Blackberry innovation and route- to- market transitions. The company reiterated its existing FY26 OSG and organic operating profit guidance of - LSD, and so we look to the call for more perspective on how to think about the unwind over the balance of the year of some F1Q tailwinds that helped support \(+1\%\) OSG and \(+2\%\) organic operating profit in the quarter.

Highlights- F1Q organic sales \(+1\%\) vs. our \(- 3\%\) , including a 4- point benefit from distributor inventory changes- US \(- 2\%\) vs. our \(- 4\%\) and Emerging markets \(+25\%\) vs. our \(+6\%\) - JD family flat vs. our \(- 3.5\%\) , el Jimador \(+16\%\) vs. our \(- 0.5\%\) and non- branded/ bulk \(- 44\%\) vs. our \(- 72\%\) - F1Q operating margin - 140 bps vs. our - 340 bps, driven primarily by stronger other income tied to the collection of substitution drawback claims though the aggregate of COGS and opex vs. our model contributed \(\sim 45\) bps to the beat
Lowlights- Developed International F1Q OSG - \(9\%\) vs. our - \(3.5\%\) - Herradura OSG 1Q - \(15\%\) vs. our flat

FY26 Guidance- Reiterated all guidance including:- Organic net sales: - LSD (vs. Consensus - \(2.5\%\) and BARCe - \(2.1\%\) )- Organic income growth: - LSD- Capex: \(125 - 135mm\) - Tax rate: \(21 - 23\%\)

**Valuation Methodology:** Our $33 price target represents a ~18.8x P/E multiple on our CY26 EPS estimate of $1.73.

**Risks which May Impede the Achievement of the Barclays Research Valuation and Price Target:** Risks to our thesis include more disruption to US spirits industry, less global demand for premium brown spirits than anticipated and/or slower adoption of emerging brands internationally, increased competition and industry fragmentation in the U.S. hurting the Jack Daniel's trademark domestically.
